    "summary": "JAMB has officially released the results of the 2026 Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination (UTME) Mock held on March 28. Additionally, over 20 CBT centres have been delisted due to technical issues. The main UTME is set to begin on April 16, 2026.",
    "fullContent": "In a recent update, the Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB) has announced the release of the 2026 UTME Mock results, which were held on Saturday, March 28, 2026. A total of 224,597 candidates registered for the mock examination, with 152,586 candidates successfully taking the test across 989 Computer-Based Test (CBT) centres nationwide.\n\nHowever, following the mock examination, JAMB has delisted over 20 CBT centres due to technical challenges and inadequate infrastructure that hindered the smooth conduct of the test. The affected centres have been removed from the list of approved examination venues for the upcoming 2026 UTME.\n\nCandidates who participated in the mock exam can check their results by sending MOCKRESULT via SMS to 55019 or 66019, using the phone number they registered with.\n\nIn a related warning, JAMB has cautioned candidates against fraudsters, particularly those operating on platforms like WhatsApp, who claim they can facilitate score inflation. JAMB made it clear that such claims are fraudulent and any candidate caught in such activities will have their registration canceled, with the possibility of having their results withheld or withdrawn if discovered after the examination.\n\nCandidates are reminded that the main UTME will commence on Thursday, April 16, 2026, and all necessary preparations should be completed in advance.",
